      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "perf(ci): use oxlint for simple boundary guards - save ~49 CI-hours/month",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\n`CI / check-additional-boundaries-a` spends time launching TypeScript-backed guard scripts for simple syntax bans. Two of those guards only need focused lint rules:\n\n- deprecated `registerHttpHandler` usage in `src` and bundled plugin code\n- raw `window.open` / `globalThis.open` usage outside the safe UI helper\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nThis replaces those two bespoke TypeScript guard scripts with focused Oxlint configs. The package scripts now route through `scripts/run-oxlint.mjs --openclaw-focused-config`, so they keep wrapper-owned sparse-target filtering and managed execution while avoiding broad type-aware/unused-disable/artifact/lock work that is unrelated to these single-rule guards.\n\nBehavior note: Oxlint's `eslint/no-restricted-properties` flags property access, while the old scripts flagged calls. I checked the current codebase for property-only false positives:\n\n- `registerHttpHandler` property non-calls: `0`\n- `window.open` / `globalThis.open` property non-calls: `0`\n\nIf a legitimate future property-only reference is needed, it can be excluded locally with a targeted Oxlint directive, for example:\n\n```ts\n// oxlint-disable-next-line eslint/no-restricted-properties -- legitimate property-only reference\nconst openRef = window.open;\n```\n\nThe same targeted directive works for a legitimate `registerHttpHandler` property-only reference.\n\n## User Impact\n\nNo product behavior change. This only reduces CI guard overhead.\n\n## What Gets Optimized\n\n`CI / check-additional-boundaries-a` runs both optimized checks. Fresh 3-run timing measured before commit on June 20, 2026:\n\n| Check | Original TS guard baseline | Final wrapper-focused Oxlint | Final delta |\n| --- | ---: | ---: | ---: |\n| `lint:plugins:no-register-http-handler` | 6.404s, 6.508s, 6.835s, avg 6.58s | 1.303s, 1.779s, 1.925s, avg 1.67s | ~4.91s saved/run |\n| `lint:ui:no-raw-window-open` | 0.575s, 1.000s, 1.288s, avg 0.95s | 1.247s, 0.893s, 0.993s, avg 1.04s | ~0.09s slower/run |\n\nCombined `check-additional-boundaries-a` delta: original avg 7.54s -> final avg 2.71s, about 4.82s saved/run.\n\nOctopool live API check for the past month, since 2026-05-21, confirms 43,925 `CI` workflow runs: 35,142 `pull_request`, 7,605 `push`, and 1,178 `workflow_dispatch`. That is the workflow-run upper bound for this job.\n\nThe 30d CI report's per-job estimate is 36,902 `CI / check-additional-boundaries-a` executions. At ~4.82s saved/run, this is about 177,873s/month, or ~49.4 runner-hours/month saved.\n\nConservative lower bound from exact mapped PR-head check runs: 433 runs in 30d, about 34.8 minutes/month saved for that exact mapped subset. This is only a floor because it excludes workflow runs that Octopool confirms exist but that were not exactly mapped to PR-head check-run rows in the local report artifact.\n\nLatest force-lock repair timing remains in the same fast-path range: direct package scripts before the wrapper repair averaged 1.41s and 1.04s; final wrapper-focused package scripts now average 1.67s and 1.04s.\n\n## Evidence\n\nFocused validation passed: `pnpm -s run lint:plugins:no-register-http-handler`, `pnpm -s run lint:ui:no-raw-window-open`, `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs test/scripts/run-oxlint.test.ts test/scripts/oxlint-config.test.ts`, `git diff --check`, and both migrated scripts with `OPENCLAW_OXLINT_FORCE_LOCK=1`. Detailed behavior proof is included below.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- Behavior addressed: `check-additional-boundaries-a` used TypeScript-backed scripts for two simple forbidden-API checks; this PR moves those checks to focused Oxlint configs behind the repo Oxlint wrapper.\n- Real environment tested: local OpenClaw source checkout on this branch, using the committed package scripts, Oxlint configs, and wrapper fast path.\n- Exact steps or command run after this patch:\n  1. `pnpm -s run lint:plugins:no-register-http-handler`\n  2. `pnpm -s run lint:ui:no-raw-window-open`\n  3. `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs test/scripts/run-oxlint.test.ts test/scripts/oxlint-config.test.ts`\n  4. `git diff --check`\n  5. `OPENCLAW_OXLINT_FORCE_LOCK=1 pnpm -s run lint:plugins:no-register-http-handler`\n  6. `OPENCLAW_OXLINT_FORCE_LOCK=1 pnpm -s run lint:ui:no-raw-window-open`\n  7. Rebuilt the deleted `scripts/check-no-raw-window-open.mjs` file collector and compared it to `pnpm exec oxlint --config config/oxlint/no-raw-window-open.json --debug=files ui/src/ui`.\n  8. Ran the current-code false-positive scan for property-only references.\n  9. Ran `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local --prompt-file <evidence>`.\n- Evidence after fix:\n  - Both focused lint commands passed through `scripts/run-oxlint.mjs --openclaw-focused-config`.\n  - Wrapper/config tests passed: 2 files, 42 tests, including focused force-lock coverage.\n  - The window-open file-selection comparison produced 223 old effective files and 223 Oxlint files, with no only-old or only-Oxlint paths.\n  - `ui/src/ui/open-external-url.ts` still contains the intentional `window.open(...)` call, and `pnpm -s run lint:ui:no-raw-window-open` passes.\n  - Current-code false-positive scan found `0` `registerHttpHandler` property non-calls and `0` `window.open` / `globalThis.open` property non-calls.\n  - Force-lock package-script proof passed for both migrated scripts.\n  - Autoreview was clean: no accepted/actionable findings; overall patch is correct (0.9).\n- Observed result after fix: the combined fresh measured delta is ~4.82s saved per `check-additional-boundaries-a` run, which projects to ~49.4 runner-hours/month from the 30d CI report estimate.\n- What was not tested: full CI was not run locally; PR CI remains the authoritative broad check.\n\n",
